                  </persName>
            . I am shopman to Mr. Morrit, a pawnbroker. I have a whip, pawned for 3 s. on the 13th of December. I cannot swear who by, but have every reason to believe that it was the prisoner. He gave his name Brown, Hamilton-row, Burton-crescent. I remarked to him that there was no such place.</p>

               <p>
            
